    <p>
      The group of all rotations of the square is simply the set of the four powers of the cycle <m>\rho = (1\ 2\ 3\ 4)</m>.  for this reason it is called a <term>cyclic group</term><fn>The phrace cyclic group applies in a more general (but similar) situation.  Namely the set of all powers of any member of a group is called a cyclic group.</fn><idx><h>cyclic group</h></idx> and is often denoted by <m>C_4</m>.  Similarly, the rotation group of an <m>n</m>-gon is usually denoted <m>C_n</m>.
    </p>


